ription":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":44,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":75,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Ralph de Abrahall de Mitcheldean was born about 1215, in Abenhall, Gloucestershire, England, his father, William Abrahall, was 26 and his mother, Mrs. William Abrahall, was 23. He married Mrs. Matilda De Abrahall. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1301, in Mitcheldean, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 87."},"et":{"about 1215–1301":"umbes 1215–1301","1215–1301":"1215–1301","1255–Female":"1255–Surnud","1282–1341":"1282–1341","1190–Male":"1190–Surnud","1194–Female":"1194–Surnud","about 1282":"umbes 1282","1190":"1190","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1301":"1301","1224":"1224","about 1215":"umbes 1215","1255":"1255","1341":"1341","1194":"1194","1282":"1282","1290":"1290","Mitcheldean, Westbury on Severn, Gloucestershire, England":"Mitcheldean, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Abenhall, Westbury-on-Severn, Gloucestershire, England":"Westbury-on-Severn, Gloucestershire, England","Abenhall, Gloucestershire, England":"Abenhall, Gloucestershire, England"},"fi":{"about 1215–1301":"noin 1215–1301","1215–1301":"1215–1301","1255–Female":"1255–Kuollut","1282–1341":"1282–1341","1190–Male":"1190–Kuollut","1194–Female":"1194–Kuollut","about 1282":"noin 1282","1190":"1190","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1